The article discusses the belief of the Administration that the CDC's new moratorium on evictions is an appropriate use of its authority to protect public health. The moratorium aims to keep Americans in their homes in areas with high COVID-19 spread. The article emphasizes that eviction moratoria have been effective in preventing the spread of the virus and keeping people housed throughout the pandemic. The Administration urges State and local governments to take further action to protect vulnerable households, including distributing the $46.5 billion in Emergency Rental Assistance funds provided through the American Rescue Plan. The article also mentions the importance of implementing eviction diversion strategies and utilizing funds from the American Rescue Plan to prevent evictions.